name: Weedle
flavorText: Its poison stinger is very powerful. Its bright-colored body is intended to warn off its enemies.

name: Kakuna
flavorText: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 40 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Beedrill
flavorText: May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds, all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon has any Special Energy attached, it is Knocked Out.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Ledyba
flavorText: These very cowardly Pokemon join together and use Reflect to protect their nest.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Ledian
flavorText: It flies through the night sky, sprinkling sparkly dust. According to some, if that dust sticks to you, good things will happen to you.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Heracross
flavorText: It roams through forests searching for sweet nectar. Although it boasts fantastic physical strength, it's not that good at flying.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, this attack does 160 more damage.

name: Celebi V
Attack1Text: Attach any number of Grass Energy cards from your hand to your Pokemon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Celebi VMAX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may heal 20 damage from each of your Grass Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Pokemon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Snover
flavorText: The berries that grow around its belly are like ice pops. Galarian Darumaka absolutely love these berries.

name: Abomasnow
flavorText: This Pokemon is known to bring blizzards. A shake of its massive body is enough to cause whiteout conditions.
Ability1Text: Your Single Strike Pokemon in play, except any Abomasnow, get +50 HP. You can't apply more than 1 Toughness Boost Ability at a time.

name: Deerling
flavorText: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokemon's fur. People use it to mark the seasons.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon's attacks do 20 less damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Sawsbuck
flavorText: They migrate according to the seasons. People can tell the season by looking at Sawsbuck's horns.
Attack2Text: If you have a Stadium in play, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Bounsweet
flavorText: When under attack, it secretes a sweet and delicious sweat. The scent only calls more enemies to it.

name: Steenee
flavorText: Any Corvisquire that pecks at this Pokemon will be greeted with a smack from its sepals followed by a sharp kick.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Tsareena
flavorText: A kick from the hardened tips of this Pokemon's legs leaves a wound in the opponent's body and soul that will never heal.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokemon's Retreat Cost.

name: Grookey
flavorText: It attacks with rapid beats of its stick. As it strikes with amazing speed, it gets more and more pumped.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

name: Thwackey
flavorText: When it's drumming out rapid beats in battle, it gets so caught up in the rhythm that it won't even notice that it's already knocked out its opponent.
Attack1Text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

name: Rillaboom
flavorText: The one with the best drumming techniques becomes the boss of the troop. It has a gentle disposition and values harmony among its group.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard any amount of Energy from your Pokemon. This attack does 30 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Zarude
flavorText: Once the vines on Zarude's body tear off, they become nutrients in the soil. This helps the plants of the forest grow.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Grass Pokemon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. If you go second and it's your first turn, search for up to 3 Grass Pokemon instead of 1. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Grass Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Blaziken V
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Blaziken VMAX
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.
Attack2Text: Choose up to 2 of your Benched Rapid Strike Pokemon and attach an Energy card from your discard pile to each of them.

name: Castform Sunny Form
flavorText: Castform changes to this form when it basks in bright sunlight. When you touch its glowing skin, it feels all dried out!
Ability1Text: If you have 8 or more Stadium cards in your discard pile, ignore all Energy in this Pokemon's attack costs.
Attack1Text: Discard a Stadium in play. If you can't, this attack does nothing.

name: Larvesta
flavorText: It protects itself with flame. Long years ago, people believed Larvesta had a nest on the sun.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Fire Energy card and attach it to this Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Volcarona
flavorText: According to legends, it was hatched from a flaming cocoon to save people and Pokemon that were suffering from the cold.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Volcanion V
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon has 10 or more damage counters on it, this attack does 150 more damage.

name: Scorbunny
flavorText: It has special pads on the backs of its feet, and one on its nose. Once it's raring to fight, these pads radiate tremendous heat.

name: Raboot
flavorText: It kicks berries right off the branches of trees and then juggles them with its feet, practicing its footwork.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Cinderace
flavorText: It's skilled at both offense and defense, and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.
Ability1Text: This Pokemon's attacks do 30 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon for each Prize card your opponent has taken (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Lapras
flavorText: Crossing icy seas is no issue for this cold-resistant Pokemon. Its smooth skin is a little cool to the touch.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Melony cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Sneasel
flavorText: It has a cunning yet savage disposition. It waits for parents to leave their nests, and then it sneaks in to steal their eggs.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Weavile
flavorText: With its claws, it leaves behind signs for its friends to find. The number of distinct signs is said to be over 500.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, if the Defending Pokemon is damaged by an attack from a Rapid Strike Pokemon, it will be Knocked Out.
Attack2Text: Search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Delibird
flavorText: It has a generous habit of sharing its food with people and Pokemon, so it's always scrounging around for more food.
Attack2Text: Put this Pokemon and all attached cards into your deck. If you do, search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Castform Rainy Form
flavorText: This is Castform's form when pelted by rain. In an experiment where it was placed in a shower, this Pokemon didn't change to this form.
Ability1Text: If you have 8 or more Stadium cards in your discard pile, ignore all Energy in this Pokemon's attack costs.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Castform Snowy Form
flavorText: This is Castform's form when caught in a hailstorm. Its whole body is chilled, and its skin is partially frozen!
Ability1Text: If you have 8 or more Stadium cards in your discard pile, ignore all Energy in this Pokemon's attack costs.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Frosty Typhoon.

name: Snorunt
flavorText: It can only survive in cold areas. It bounces happily around, even in environments as cold as −150 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Froslass
flavorText: It spits out cold air of nearly −60 degrees Fahrenheit to freeze its quarry. It brings frozen prey back to its lair and neatly lines them up.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may attach a Water Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Pokemon.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Spheal
flavorText: Its body is covered in fluffy fur. The fur keeps it from feeling cold while it is rolling on ice.

name: Sealeo
flavorText: Be it Spheal or a Poke Ball, it will spin any round object on its nose with the greatest of ease.

name: Walrein
flavorText: It shatters drift ice with its strong tusks. Its thick layer of blubber repels enemy attacks.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon. Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Tapu Fini
flavorText: Although it's called a guardian deity, terrible calamities sometimes befall those who recklessly approach Tapu Fini.
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Put an Energy attached to this Pokemon into your hand.

name: Sobble
flavorText: When it gets wet, its skin changes color, and this Pokemon becomes invisible as if it were camouflaged.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 Basic Rapid Strike Pokemon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Drizzile
flavorText: Highly intelligent but also very lazy, it keeps enemies out of its territory by laying traps everywhere.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Inteleon
flavorText: Its nictitating membranes let it pick out foes' weak points so it can precisely blast them with water that shoots from its fingertips at Mach 3.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may put 2 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokemon.

name: Rapid Strike Urshifu
flavorText: This form of Urshifu is a strong believer in defeating foes by raining many blows down on them. Its strikes are nonstop, flowing like a river.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 damage for each of your Rapid Strike Pokemon in play.

name: Ice Rider Calyrex V
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Ice Rider Calyrex VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: You may discard up to 2 Energy from this Pokemon. If you do, this attack does 120 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Mareep
flavorText: Rubbing its fleece generates electricity. You'll want to pet it because it's cute, but if you use your bare hand, you'll get a painful shock.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon's attacks do 20 less damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Flaaffy
flavorText: It stores electricity in its fluffy fleece. If it stores up too much, it will start to go bald in those patches.

name: Ampharos
flavorText: Its tail shines bright and strong. It has been prized since long ago as a beacon for sailors.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Your opponent reveals their hand. If you find any Energy cards there, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Blitzle
flavorText: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Zebstrika
flavorText: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.
Attack1Text: If 1 of your other Rapid Strike Pokemon used an attack during your last turn, this attack does 90 more damage.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 90 damage for each heads.

name: Thundurus
flavorText: As it flies around, it shoots lightning all over the place and causes forest fires. It is therefore disliked.
Attack1Text: You may attach a Lightning Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Zeraora V
Attack1Text: If 1 of your other Rapid Strike Pokemon used an attack during your last turn, this attack also does 160 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Galarian Slowpoke
flavorText: Because Galarian Slowpoke eat the seeds of a plant that grows only in Galar, their tails have developed a spicy flavor.

name: Gastly
flavorText: With its gas-like body, it can sneak into any place it desires. However, it can be blown away by wind.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Haunter
flavorText: If you get the feeling of being watched in darkness when nobody is around, Haunter is there.

name: Gengar
flavorText: It is said to emerge from darkness to steal the lives of those who become lost in mountains.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokemon, search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Galarian Articuno V
Ability1Text: You must discard 2 cards from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw a card.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Ralts
flavorText: If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokemon, its body warms up slightly.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Kirlia
flavorText: It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the space around it and see into the future.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 Kirlia and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Gardevoir
flavorText: To protect its Trainer, it will expend all its psychic power to create a small black hole.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may look at the top 2 cards of your deck and attach any number of basic Energy cards you find there to your Pokemon in any way you like. Put the other cards into your hand.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Psychic Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Shuppet
flavorText: There's a proverb that says, "Shun the house where Shuppet gather in the growing dusk."

name: Banette
flavorText: Resentment at being cast off made it spring into being. Some say that treating it well will satisfy it, and it will once more become a stuffed toy.
Attack1Text: Put up to 7 damage counters on this Pokemon. This attack does 20 damage for each damage counter you placed in this way.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Cresselia
flavorText: Those who sleep holding Cresselia's feather are assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent the crescent moon.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Psychic Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokemon. If you go second and it's your first turn, instead search for up to 3 Psychic Energy cards and attach them to 1 of your Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: If you have at least 5 Energy in play, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Golett
flavorText: This Pokemon was created from clay. It received orders from its master many thousands of years ago, and it still follows those orders to this day.

name: Golurk
flavorText: There's a theory that inside Golurk is a perpetual motion machine that produces limitless energy, but this belief hasn't been proven.
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon has a Pokemon Tool attached, this attack does 90 more damage.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Swirlix
flavorText: The sweet smell of cotton candy perfumes Swirlix's fluffy fur. This Pokemon spits out sticky string to tangle up its enemies.
Attack1Text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Slurpuff
flavorText: Slurpuff's fur contains a lot of air, making it soft to the touch and lighter than it looks.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. Put a number of cards up to the number of heads from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Inkay
flavorText: By exposing foes to the blinking of its luminescent spots, Inkay demoralizes them, and then it seizes the chance to flee.

name: Malamar
flavorText: It's said that Malamar's hypnotic powers played a role in certain history-changing events.
Attack1Text: Reveal any number of Rapid Strike cards from your hand. This attack does 40 damage for each card you revealed in this way. Then, shuffle those cards into your deck.

name: Hatenna
flavorText: If this Pokemon senses a strong emotion, it will run away as fast as it can. It prefers areas without people.

name: Hattrem
flavorText: Using the braids on its head, it pummels foes to get them to quiet down. One blow from those braids would knock out a professional boxer.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Hatterene
flavorText: If you're too loud around it, you risk being torn apart by the claws on its tentacle. This Pokemon is also known as the Forest Witch.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may switch your Active Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon. If you do, your opponent switches their Active Pokemon with 1 of their Benched Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Shadow Rider Calyrex V
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, they can't play any Special Energy or Stadium cards from their hand.
Attack2Text: Choose 2 of your opponent's Pokemon and put 5 damage counters on each of them.

name: Shadow Rider Calyrex VMAX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Psychic Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Benched Psychic Pokemon. If you attached Energy to a Pokemon in this way, draw 2 cards.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Psychic Energy attached to all of your Pokemon.

name: Diglett
flavorText: It burrows through the ground at a shallow depth. It leaves raised earth in its wake, making it easy to spot.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokemon.

name: Dugtrio
flavorText: These Diglett triplets dig over 60 miles below sea level. No one knows what it's like underground.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 60 damage for each heads. If all of them are heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokemon.

name: Galarian Farfetch'd
flavorText: The stalks of leeks are thicker and longer in the Galar region. Farfetch'd that adapted to these stalks took on a unique form.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Galarian Sirfetch'd
flavorText: After deflecting attacks with its hard leaf shield, it strikes back with its sharp leek stalk. The leek stalk is both weapon and food.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon has a Pokemon Tool attached, this attack does 90 more damage, and this attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Galarian Zapdos V
Ability1Text: This Pokemon's attacks cost Colorless less for each of your opponent's Pokemon V in play.
Attack1Text: Before doing damage, discard a Special Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Gallade
flavorText: Sharply attuned to others' wishes for help, this Pokemon seeks out those in need and aids them in battle.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.
Attack2Text: This attack does 60 damage for each of your opponent's Pokemon V in play.

name: Galarian Yamask
flavorText: It's said that this Pokemon was formed when an ancient clay tablet was drawn to a vengeful spirit.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Galarian Runerigus
flavorText: Never touch its shadowlike body, or you'll be shown the horrific memories behind the picture carved into it.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokemon VMAX (even if this Pokemon is Knocked Out), put damage counters on the Attacking Pokemon equal to the damage done to this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Crabrawler
flavorText: Crabrawler has been known to mistake Exeggutor for a coconut tree and climb it. The enraged Exeggutor shakes it off and stomps it.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

name: Crabominable
flavorText: Before it stops to think, it just starts pummeling. There are records of its turning back avalanches with a flurry of punches.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 90 damage for each heads.

name: Rockruff
flavorText: When it rubs the rocks on its neck against you, that's proof of its love for you. However, the rocks are sharp, so the gesture is quite painful!
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Lycanroc
flavorText: They live alone without forming packs. They will only listen to orders from Trainers who can draw out their true power.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each Single Strike Pokemon in your discard pile.

name: Passimian
flavorText: Passimian live in groups of about 20, with each member performing an assigned role. Through cooperation, the group survives.
Ability1Text: Your Rapid Strike Pokemon's attacks do 30 more damage to your opponent's Benched Pokemon V and Benched Pokemon-GX (before applying Weakness and Resistance). You can't apply more than 1 Throwing Coach Ability at a time.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Sandaconda V
Ability1Text: This Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Sandaconda VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack also does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: Move any amount of Energy from your Pokemon to your other Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Clobbopus
flavorText: Its tentacles tear off easily, but it isn't alarmed when that happens—it knows they'll grow back. It's about as smart as a three-year-old.

name: Grapploct
flavorText: Searching for an opponent to test its skills against, it emerges onto land. Once the battle is over, it returns to the sea.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, your opponent's Active Pokemon's Retreat Cost is ColorlessColorless more.
Attack1Text: If you have the same number of cards in your hand as your opponent, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Kubfu
flavorText: If Kubfu pulls the long white hair on its head, its fighting spirit heightens and power wells up from the depths of its belly.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a basic Energy card and attach it to this Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Koffing
flavorText: It adores polluted air. Some claim that Koffing used to be more plentiful in the Galar region than they are now.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Weezing
flavorText: Very rarely, a sudden mutation can result in two small Koffing twins becoming conjoined as a Weezing.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused. Attach a Darkness Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Darkness Energy attached to all of your Pokemon.

name: Galarian Weezing
flavorText: Long ago, during a time when droves of factories fouled the air with pollution, Weezing changed into this form for some reason.
Ability1Text: Each basic Darkness Energy attached to your Pokemon that have "Weezing" in their name provides DarknessDarkness Energy. You can't apply more than 1 Energy Factory Ability at a time.

name: Galarian Moltres V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Darkness Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokemon. You can't use more than 1 Direflame Wings Ability each turn.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Galarian Slowking
flavorText: While chanting strange spells, this Pokemon combines its internal toxins with what it's eaten, creating strange potions.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may choose 1 of your Pokemon and flip a coin. If heads, heal 90 damage from that Pokemon. If tails, put 3 damage counters on that Pokemon.

name: Galarian Slowking V
Attack1Text: Discard a card from your hand. If you do, draw 3 cards.
Attack2Text: At the end of your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon will be Knocked Out.

name: Galarian Slowking VMAX
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned. During Pokemon Checkup, put 12 damage counters on that Pokemon instead of 1.

name: Qwilfish
flavorText: The small spikes covering its body developed from scales. They inject a toxin that causes fainting.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is in the Active Spot and is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokemon, put 6 damage counters on the Attacking Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Seviper
flavorText: Constant polishing makes the edge of the blade on its tail extremely sharp. It's Zangoose's archrival.
Attack1Text: If you played a Single Strike Supporter card from your hand during this turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Spiritomb
flavorText: It was bound to a fissure in an Odd Keystone as punishment for misdeeds 500 years ago.
Attack1Text: For each Pokemon in your opponent's discard pile, put 1 damage counter on your opponent's Pokemon in any way you like. If you placed any damage counters in this way, your opponent shuffles all Pokemon from their discard pile into their deck.

name: Liepard V
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may discard a Pokemon Tool from a Pokemon (yours or your opponent's).
Attack1Text: You may put this Pokemon and all attached cards into your hand.

name: Venipede
flavorText: Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokemon that try to prey on it.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Whirlipede
flavorText: It is usually motionless, but when attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Scolipede
flavorText: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is Poisoned, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Single Strike Urshifu
flavorText: Inhabiting the mountains of a distant region, this Pokemon races across sheer cliffs, training its legs and refining its moves.
Attack1Text: If your opponent has a Stadium in play, discard it.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon has any damage counters on it, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Aron
flavorText: When it evolves, it sheds the steel carapace that covered its whole body and develops a new one.

name: Lairon
flavorText: It habitually shows off its strength with the size of sparks it creates by ramming its steel body into boulders.

name: Aggron
flavorText: While seeking iron for food, it digs tunnels by breaking through bedrock with its steel horns.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: This attack also does 30 damage to each of your Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Metagross V
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon and your opponent's Active Pokemon have the same amount of Energy attached, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Metagross VMAX
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's Max Rush attack does 150 more damage.

name: Cobalion
flavorText: It has a body and heart of steel. It worked with its allies to punish people when they hurt Pokemon.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Tauros
flavorText: They live in groups. The one with the longest, thickest, and most-scarred horns is the boss of the herd.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon. This Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Porygon
flavorText: It was built 20 years ago by scientists who dreamed of exploring space. Their dreams have yet to come true.

name: Porygon2
flavorText: Even though it doesn't die in the vacuum of space, it can't move around very well in zero gravity.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

name: Porygon-Z
flavorText: A faulty update was added to its programming. Its behavior is noticeably strange, so the experiment may have been a failure.
Ability1Text: Whenever you attach an Energy card from your hand to this Pokemon during your turn, you may make your opponent's Active Pokemon Confused.
Attack1Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Blissey V
Ability1Text: Whenever you attach an Energy card from your hand to this Pokemon, remove all Special Conditions from it.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to this Pokemon. If you did any damage with this attack, you may attach up to 3 Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokemon.

name: Zangoose
flavorText: Its fur would all stand on end if it smelled a Seviper nearby. Its sharp claws tear up its foes.
